<p>January 20</p>

<p>China claims: China's National Health Commission said human to human transmission was 'affirmative' after cases cropped up in healthcare workers. </p>

<p>Critics claim: China filed a patent for the drug Remdesivir, seen as one of the best potential weapons against COVID-19, the day after it finally confirmed human transmission of the disease. The application was made by Wuhan Institute of Virology, the top-secret bio-laboratory at the centre of concerns about a possible leak of the disease from its research on bats, and the country's Military Medicine Institute</p>

<p>January 23</p>

<p>China claims: Beijing finally puts Wuhan under lockdown, as infections continue to soar and after millions had travelled to and from the city for Lunar New Year celebrations. </p>

<p>Critics claim: The move comes despite Xi Jinping knowing about the spread of the virus by January 7.  China has since admitted destroying early samples of coronavirus in January, but claims it was acting in the interests of public health and denies stonewalling sample requests from other countries.</p>

<p>March 1 </p>

<p>China claims: It has been open and honest with the world about the spread of coronavirus</p>

